Description: Large fragment of East Greek pottery oenochoe, comprising rim, probably trefoil, neck, handle and upper body; interior reserved save for band at rim; Handle and neck glazed except for area behind handle; thick wavy band on shoulder; two bands on belly and one on worn lower body. Rather coarse pink-buff clay with little mica. Brown sticky remains inside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 101 (= Well 5)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.329)
Stacey et al 2010 / Coatings and contents: investigations of residues on four fragmentary sixth-century BC vessels from Naukratis (Egypt) (p.20, fig.1d, p.21, table.1, fig.2)
